data.prayer: Lord of the Harvest, please send out workers into the the state of Jász-Nagykun-Szolnok, Hungary.
data.verse: Then he said to his disciples, “The harvest is plentiful but the workers are few. Ask the Lord of the harvest, therefore, to send out workers into his harvest field.

data.prayer: Jesus, make the 338,938 people in the state of Jász-Nagykun-Szolnok who claim to know you, brave enough to let the Bible weigh their thoughts and intentions today.
data.verse: For the word of God is living and powerful, and sharper than any two-edged sword, piercing even to the division of soul and spirit, and of joints and marrow, and is a discerner of the thoughts and intents of the heart.

data.prayer: Spirit, renew the call of John the Baptist in the state of Jász-Nagykun-Szolnok. Send out bold servants who will call all to repent.
data.verse: Repent, for the kingdom of heaven is at hand.

data.prayer: Jesus, I pray that all the Jew, Hungarian-speaking people will remember and turn to you, Lord God. May all the Jew, Hungarian-speaking people worship before you. For the kingdom of the Jew, Hungarian-speaking people is yours.
Father, let love abound more and more in the church of Jász-Nagykun-Szolnok, Hungary.
data.verse: And this is my prayer: that your love may abound more and more in knowledge and depth of insight

data.prayer: Spirit, help the fearful in Jász-Nagykun-Szolnok, Hungary to submit to God and resist the devil.
data.verse: Submit yourselves, then, to God. Resist the devil, and he will flee from you.

data.section_summary:
the state of Jász-Nagykun-Szolnok, Hungary has a population of 403,600.

We estimate Jász-Nagykun-Szolnok has 12,331 people who might know Jesus, 338,938 people who might know about Jesus culturally, and 52,331 people who do not know Jesus.

This is 1 believer for every 32 neighbors who need Jesus.

data.prayer: Spirit, fill the 12,331 believers in the state of Jász-Nagykun-Szolnok with tears, because God is not obeyed by those around them.
data.verse: Streams of tears flow from my eyes, for your law is not obeyed.
